The Special Investigative Unit will be probing the Talana shack project in Tzaneen Limpopo. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The Special Investigative Unit will be probing the Talana shack project in Tzaneen, Limpopo. The Limpopo government came under fire after it paid over R2-million for the shacks, amounting to at least R60,000 per shack. READ: Sisulu refuses to comment on Limpopo shack saga Limpopo Premier Stan Mathabatha denies any wrongdoing. Mathabatha says people must stop pointing fingers until the investigation is concluded.